(40, 5, 19, 45, 13, 8, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Love and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of fulfilling the law through actions. Matthew highlights the significance of obeying commandments, while Romans states that love is the fulfillment of the law. This connection highlights how love embodies the essence of the commandments.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 19, 40, 11, 11, 11, 'least in the kingdom of heaven', 'Greatness in the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of greatness in the kingdom of heaven. Matthew 5:19 discusses the distinction between those who teach and follow commandments, while Matthew 11:11 highlights John the Baptist''s status compared to the least in the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 19, 54, 6, 3, 4, 'teach men so', 'Teaching and Commandments Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of teaching sound doctrine and adhering to commandments. Matthew highlights the consequences of breaking commandments, while Timothy warns against teaching otherwise. This connection highlights the value placed on proper teaching in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 19, 19, 119, 6, 6, NULL, 'Respect for Commandments', 'This connection highlights the importance of respecting and teaching God''s commandments. Both passages emphasize the consequences of how one engages with these commandments, linking obedience to honor in the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 45, 10, 2, 3, 'righteousness shall exceed the righteousness', 'Righteousness and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness, where Matthew emphasizes exceeding the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, while Romans discusses ignorance of God''s righteousness. Both passages stress the importance of understanding and submitting to true righteousness.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 50, 3, 9, 9, 'righteousness shall exceed the righteousness', 'Righteousness and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between human righteousness and divine righteousness. Both passages emphasize the necessity of a righteousness that surpasses mere legal adherence, pointing towards faith in Christ as the true source of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 45, 9, 30, 32, 'righteousness shall exceed the righteousness', 'Righteousness and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees and the righteousness attained by faith. Both passages emphasize that true righteousness is not achieved through works of the law but through faith, indicating a deeper understanding of what it means to be righteous.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 42, 16, 14, 15, 'your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness', 'Righteousness and Self-Justification', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness, as both passages address the inadequacy of the Pharisees'' self-justification. Matthew emphasizes the need for a righteousness that exceeds theirs, while Luke critiques their justification before men, indicating a deeper moral failure.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 40, 23, 2, 5, 'righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees', 'Righteousness and Hypocrisy', 'Both passages emphasize the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, contrasting it with their hypocritical actions. Matthew 5:20 warns that true righteousness must exceed theirs, while Matthew 23:2-5 critiques their failure to practice what they preach.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 43, 3, 3, 5, 'enter into the kingdom of heaven', 'Righteousness and Kingdom Entry', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of meeting specific conditions to enter the kingdom of God. Matthew highlights exceeding the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, while John stresses being born again of water and the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 20, 40, 23, 23, 28, 'righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees', 'Righteousness of the Pharisees', 'This connection highlights the contrast between true righteousness and the superficial righteousness exhibited by the scribes and Pharisees. Both passages emphasize the importance of inner purity over outward appearances.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 21, 5, 5, 17, 17, 'Thou shalt not kill', 'Connection of Commandments Against Killing', 'This connection highlights the continuity of the commandment against killing. Both passages emphasize the prohibition of murder, establishing a moral standard.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 21, 2, 20, 13, 13, 'Thou shalt not kill', 'Connection of Commandments on Killing', 'This connection highlights the commandment against killing found in both passages. Matthew 5:21 references the prohibition from Exodus 20:13, emphasizing the continuity of moral teaching.', 'quotation', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
