(40, 5, 21, 4, 35, 16, 21, 'Thou shalt not kill', 'Connection on Murder and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the seriousness of murder and the consequences that follow. Matthew 5:21 references the commandment against killing, while Numbers 35:16-21 details the penalties for murder, highlighting the moral and legal implications of taking a life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 21, 5, 21, 7, 9, 'Thou shalt not kill', 'Connection of Innocent Blood and Killing', 'This connection highlights the theme of guilt associated with bloodshed. Both passages address the consequences of killing and the need for mercy regarding innocent blood.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 21, 1, 9, 5, 6, 'Thou shalt not kill', 'Connection on the Value of Life', 'Both passages emphasize the sanctity of human life and the consequences of taking it. Matthew 5:21 references the command against killing, while Genesis 9:5-6 outlines the severe repercussions for shedding blood, highlighting the seriousness of this moral principle.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 22, 62, 3, 14, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Anger and Hatred', 'Both passages emphasize the seriousness of harboring negative feelings towards others. Matthew warns against anger and insults, while 1 John equates hatred with murder, highlighting the moral gravity of such emotions.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
