(40, 5, 22, 49, 4, 26, 27, 'angry with his brother without a cause', 'Anger and Its Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of managing anger. Matthew warns against anger leading to judgment, while Ephesians advises not to let anger linger, suggesting that unresolved anger can lead to negative outcomes.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 22, 59, 3, 6, 6, 'in danger of hell fire', 'Connection of Anger and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the destructive nature of anger and harmful speech. Matthew warns of judgment for anger and insults, while James describes the tongue as a fire that defiles and is set on fire of hell.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 22, 56, 3, 2, 2, 'angry with his brother without a cause', 'Anger and Meekness in Relationships', 'This connection highlights the importance of controlling anger and speaking kindly to others. Both passages emphasize the need for gentleness and avoiding harmful speech towards others.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 5, 22, 40, 10, 28, 28, 'hell fire', 'Connection of Anger and Hell', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of actions leading to hell. Matthew 5:22 warns against anger and insults, while Matthew 10:28 speaks of fearing the one who can destroy both soul and body in hell.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
