(40, 5, 23, 42, 19, 8, 8, 'thy brother hath ought against thee', 'Restoration and Reconciliation Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of reconciliation and restitution. In Matthew, the emphasis is on addressing grievances with others before offering gifts, while in Luke, Zaccheus demonstrates this by restoring what he has wrongfully taken.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
